# MaxView UI / MWx Design Standards

## CSS variables — always use tokens

Never hardcode colours, shadows, or borders. Use the CSS custom properties from the project's global stylesheet:

```css
/* GOOD */
background: var(--bg-primary);
color: var(--text-secondary);
border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);

/* BAD */
background: #ffffff;
color: #666;
border: 1px solid #ddd;
```

## Dark mode

Dark mode is handled by a `[data-theme="dark"]` selector. Do not add manual dark-mode overrides via inline styles or JS theme checks:

```tsx
// BAD
const isDark = document.body.dataset.theme === 'dark';
style={{ color: isDark ? '#fff' : '#000' }}

// GOOD — use a CSS variable and let the theme do the work
style={{ color: 'var(--text-primary)' }}
```

## MWx Design System components

When the feature requires a UI element that exists in the MWx Design System component library:

1. Search the project's component registry or design-system directory first.
2. Use the canonical MWx component rather than building a bespoke one.
3. Pass only the documented props — do not override internal MWx component styles with inline overrides.

## Co-located stylesheets (CSS Modules)

All new components use CSS Modules:

```
src/client/components/
  ShiftCard.tsx
  ShiftCard.module.css   ← import styles from './ShiftCard.module.css'
```

Reference classes with `styles.camelCase` or `styles['kebab-case']`. Do not use global class names for new components.

## Inline styles

Reserve inline styles for values that are truly dynamic (driven by runtime state only):

```tsx
// GOOD — dynamic value from state
style={{ opacity: isDragging ? 0.5 : 1, width: `${panelWidth}px` }}

// BAD — static values belong in CSS
style={{ padding: '8px 12px', borderRadius: '4px' }}
```

## Transitions

- Micro-interactions (hover, focus, button states): `transition: all 0.2s ease`
- Panel / modal animations: `transition: all 0.3s ease`

## Spacing and sizing

Use the project's spacing scale: 4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32 px. Avoid arbitrary magic numbers.
